                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> BURLEY. Convention (indented) made the year Lodovic [King of France] returned
                  from England [i.e. <origDate when="1217">1217</origDate>], for

                  a term of 6 years from the feast of St. Martin, by which

                  <persName>
                           <forename>Ysabella</forename> des <surname>Rodiz</surname>
                        </persName> and
                  <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> her son</persName> demise to
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Bernard</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                  and <persName>
                           <forename>Jordan</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Warin</surname>
                        </persName>, three bovates 
                  of land in <placeName key="place_103077">Birle</placeName>, which <persName>
                           <forename>Owain</forename>
                        </persName> held, 
                  for 11s. of silver, which the said Ralph and Jordan gave for a recognition, and a rent of 8s. per annum. 
                  . </p>
                  </msItem>
